ted","message":"","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-08-03T02:45:42.394Z","updated_at":"2018-08-03T02:45:42.394Z","additional_data":{"old_title":"Local files reading from web using `brave://`","new_title":"Local files reading from the web using `brave://`"},"actor":{"username":"metnew","cleared":true,"url":"/metnew","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/038/544/baa5f77ccb2413a76bf96b3253ba88024ab50a33_original.jpeg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"brave","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":3135522,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"## Patch\n\nI saw the Brave team's patch for #375329. As far as I remember, they made a check to not convert `brave://` to `file://`. However, `brave://` is nested from `AsarProtocolHandler`(correct name?) that adds `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` header to all requests. \n\nThe patch is simple 😈","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-08-03T02:53:37.284Z","updated_at":"2018-08-03T02:53:37.284Z","actor":{"username":"metnew","cleared":true,"url":"/metnew","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/038/544/baa5f77ccb2413a76bf96b3253ba88024ab50a33_original.jpeg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"brave","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":3135544,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"### Typo\n\n`brave://` protocol was introduced as a replacement for `file://` protocol that was nesting `AsarProtocolHandler`(or something like that) in `brave/muon`.\n\n\u003e That's from my understanding. Probably, Brave will use `brave://` similarly to `chrome://` in future (as a browser-level protocol handler for internal config or etc.).","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-08-03T03:08:02.650Z","updated_at":"2018-08-03T03:08:02.650Z","actor":{"username":"metnew","cleared":true,"url":"/metnew","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/038/544/baa5f77ccb2413a76bf96b3253ba88024ab50a33_original.jpeg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"brave","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":3135611,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"\u003e I've contacted @diracdeltas through security@brave.com\n\n### Impact\nNote that it's a generic issue: it also allows local files downloading/inclusion through `brave://`.\n\n\u003e ~~I hope that Brave will not ignore my messages as usual and read this:~~\n\n### Patch\n\n#### `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` - quick fix\nRemove `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` headers from `AsarProtocolHandler` response\n\n#### `FileProtocolHandler` vs `AsarProtocolHandler`\n\n`brave://` should behave as `file://` (`net::FileProtocolHandler`). That's probably impossible. \n\nIf `brave://` inherits `AsarProtocolHandler`, you have to apply the same rules to this protocol as `FileProtocolHandler` has (i.e., make it inaccessible from the web). This likely requires changes on the Chromium level.\n\nFrom the other side, removing `AsarProtocolHandler` from the codebase is probably impossible because of Electron requirements (not sure).\n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-08-03T03:57:26.482Z","updated_at":"2018-08-03T03:57:26.482Z","actor":{"username":"metnew","cleared":true,"url":"/metnew","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/038/544/baa5f77ccb2413a76bf96b3253ba88024ab50a33_original.jpeg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"brave","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":3135688,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"This vulnerability was fixed in https://github.com/brave/muon/commit/85de41ea3f6b069e0e4f628da7365e3f4e5c9cf2\n\n\u003e Thanks for the quick fix @brave ","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-08-03T04:42:21.416Z","updated_at":"2018-08-03T04:42:21.416Z","actor":{"username":"metnew","cleared":true,"url":"/metnew","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/038/544/baa5f77ccb2413a76bf96b3253ba88024ab50a33_original.jpeg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"brave","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":3139006,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugResolved","message":"Closing since we received by email and resolved it last night. Figuring out bounty now","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-08-03T21:49:13.622Z","updated_at":"2018-08-03T21:49:13.622Z","actor":{"username":"diracdeltas","cleared":false,"url":"/diracdeltas","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/115/616/4e2016543ea3e299dcadd088be7d0225de3419e0_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"reporter":{"username":"metnew","url":"/metnew"},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"brave","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":3139051,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BountyAwarded","message":"","automated_response":false,"creat